                        <h3>How Beginning Golfers Can Make Golf More Fun!</h3>
                        <p>For a beginner, golf can be too competitive, stuffy, and very intimidating. There are way too many complicated rules and expectations. Relax. There may be a time when you want to keep score, know all the rules, or play in a tournament, but until that time comes, try these suggestions:</p>
                        <ol>
                            <li>Don't keep score.</li>
                            <li>Play from the short tees.</li>
                            <li>Only count shots when you hit the ball.</li>
                            <li>Play in your tennis shoes; be comfortable.</li>
                            <li>Move your ball away from trees and rocks.</li>
                            <li>Skip a hole if you need a break.</li>
                            <li>Just chip and putt if you want to.</li>
                            <li>Play with only a couple of clubs and a putter.</li>
                            <li>Enjoy the scenery.</li>
                            <li>Talk, tell jokes, laugh at each others’ bad shots.</li>
                            <li>Be enthusiastic! Give high fives!</li>
                            <li>Bring your kids.</li>
                            <li>Tee the ball up everywhere.</li>
                        </ol>
                        <p>Squaw Creek Golf Course offers “on course” lessons to help you feel more comfortable on the course. A member of our staff will go with you onto the course to learn basic etiquette and rules. These lessons are free of charge. Call us at 817-441-8185 and schedule yours today!</p>
